# Core workflow gates (Cursor)

This is a **thin mirror** of the canonical rules in `/.claude/`.

## Canonical entrypoint

- Read and follow `/.claude/CLAUDE.md`

## Canonical rules (details)

- `/.claude/rules/00-core.md`
- `/.claude/rules/05-design-log.md`
- `/.claude/rules/10-architecture.md`
- `/.claude/rules/20-jsdoc.md`
- `/.claude/rules/30-react.md`
- `/.claude/rules/40-typescript.md`

## Non-negotiables (summary)

- **Design log gate**: if it triggers, create/approve the design log before coding
- **Architecture**: always separate business logic from UI (lib → hook → UI)
- **Explicitness**: prefer explicit intent over implicit conventions
- **Docs**: exported components/hooks/functions document params + returns
- **Checks**: after substantive edits run `npm run biome:ci`.
  Only run `npm run build` when explicitly requested.

